										<div class="post_wrapper author">
											<div id="about_the_author">
												<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/marylanepotter/"><img src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a8ac4a60ffa0712749c1bd9f4c15ae47?s=100&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g" width="100" height="100" alt="Avatar" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 photo avatar-default" /></a></div>
												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/marylanepotter/">Mary Lane Potter</a></h6>
													Mary Lane Potter’s books include <i>Strangers and Sojourners: Stories from the Lowcountry</i>and the novel <i>A Woman of Salt</i>(both from Counterpoint). Her essays have appeared in <i>Parabola, Witness, River Teeth, Tiferet, Tablet, Sufi, ARTS</i>, and more.																									</div>
